<p> Below is the syntax for my command line arguments.</p>  <pre class="lang-C prettyprint-override"><code>./main [-var1 value] [-var2 value] [-var3 value] </code></pre>  <p><code>var1</code>,<code>var2</code>  and <code>var3</code>  are strings.   for ex:  <code>var1</code> is aaa,  <code>var2</code> is bbb, and  <code>var3</code> is ccc.</p>  <p>However for a similar case with single characters options, for example <code>a</code>, <code>b</code> and <code>c</code> as shown below</p>  <pre class="lang-C prettyprint-override"><code>./main [-a value] [-b value] [-c value]  </code></pre>  <p><code>getopt(argc, argv, "a:b:c:");</code> can be used. Is there a similar way to process <code>var1</code>,<code>var2</code>  and <code>var3</code> for my program. </p>